<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="G" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Gall1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Gall,</orth> subst. 1) the bile: <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.2.199" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 2, 199</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.5.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 5, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 4.1.27" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.3.93" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 3, 93</bibl>.<lb />2) an ingredient of ink: <bibl n="shak. tn 3.2.52" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 2, 52</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.1.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 1, 101</bibl>.
<lb />3) any thing bitter and disagreeable: <emph>thy</emph> <cit><quote>honey turns to g., thy joy to grief,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 889" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 889</bibl></cit>. Pilgr <bibl n="shak. luc 889" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 889</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.322" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 322</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 2.2.144" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 2, 144</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.5.30" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.1.200" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 1, 200</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.5.94" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 5, 94</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.4.127" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 4, 127</bibl>. cf. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.1.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 1, 101</bibl>.
<lb />4) bitterness of mind, rancor: <cit><quote>to tie the g. up in the slanderous tongue,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.199" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 199</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thou grievest my g.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.237" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 237</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.2.30" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 2, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.2.16" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 2, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.152" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 152</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.193" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 193</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.193" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 193</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.605" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 605</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.4.292" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 4, 292</bibl>. cf. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.2.52" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 2, 52</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.2.199" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 2, 199</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.5.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 5, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.3.93" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 3, 93</bibl>. The abstr. for the concr.: <cit><quote>out, g.!</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 5.1.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 1, 40</bibl></cit>.
